some behavior change that

00:47:37.090 --> 00:47:39.130
could disrupt a lot
of these contagions.

00:47:39.130 --> 00:47:40.510
But we don't do them.

00:47:40.510 --> 00:47:42.410
And I think a good
example of that

00:47:42.410 --> 00:47:46.062
is bed nets for malaria
control, where this

00:47:46.062 --> 00:47:47.270
is a very simple thing to do.

00:47:47.270 --> 00:47:48.070
You get a bed net.

00:47:48.070 --> 00:47:49.460
You sleep under it every night.

00:47:49.460 --> 00:47:51.600
And you don't get malaria,
this killer disease.

00:47:51.600 --> 00:47:54.720
Well, when they first started
distributing those nets,

00:47:54.720 --> 00:47:57.000
like 20% of the
people used them.

00:47:57.000 --> 00:47:59.410
80% just thought, oh, this
is the most fancy thing

00:47:59.410 --> 00:48:00.730
I've ever owned.

00:48:00.730 --> 00:48:02.300
I'm going to keep
it in this chest

00:48:02.300 --> 00:48:04.249
and when my fancy
uncle comes over,

00:48:04.249 --> 00:48:05.540
I'll show him that I have this.

00:48:05.540 --> 00:48:08.820
Or I'll use it for a wedding
veil, or fishing nets,

00:48:08.820 --> 00:48:10.800
or whatever.

00:48:10.800 --> 00:48:13.030
So that's why so
much of public health

00:48:13.030 --> 00:48:16.120
is about coming up
with ways so that we

00:48:16.120 --> 00:48:18.490
don't have to ask people to
change their behavior that

00:48:18.490 --> 00:48:19.480
much.

00:48:19.480 --> 00:48:24.250
So how do you engineer our
architecture, or our economy,

00:48:24.250 --> 00:48:27.130
or all these other incentives
that shape human behavior?

00:48:27.130 --> 00:48:29.910
How do you change that
part, so that doing

00:48:29.910 --> 00:48:33.070
the disease-free or
disease-minimizing behavior

00:48:33.070 --> 00:48:34.220
becomes easy?

00:48:34.220 --> 00:48:36.806
It has to be the path
of least resistance.

00:48:36.806 --> 00:48:40.520
We see even in hospitals that
doctors don't wash their hands

00:48:40.520 --> 00:48:41.780
between patients.

00:48:41.780 --> 00:48:45.820
I mean, that's kind of an
amazing thing-- so simple.

00:48:45.820 --> 00:48:48.080
But simple solutions,
when it comes up

00:48:48.080 --> 00:48:51.080
to complex human behaviors,
turn out to be not so simple.

